    {
      "id": "ea38543ab983cc50dc9f5f956e5ba84b9ca05c14",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-19 00:30:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nSorry, give - only for holding this patch a bit.  Because\n\n1. I do not see the problem how only landing 13392 will cause any problem. \n2.This is temporary patch, and will not needed after dne2 is landed, plus this will cause a lot conflicts for dne2 landing. \n\nFan Yong, if I miss anything, please correct me.  And also could you please tell me which patch are needed by this one?  And can that be landed after dne2 ? Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c7b8c25a833bf83862385c5268c7f8a50cbc2d9c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-19 12:10:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIn fact, the patch 13392 can be applied on current master, but if without the dependent patches 13709 and 13710, the sanity-lfsck will fail. That is the most direct affect.\n\nOn the other hand, the patch 13710 fixed the confused remote transaction logic: if without such patch, some of LFSCK RPC will be triggered when remote transaction start, but some will be triggered when remote transaction stop; in further, it may cause two OUT RPCs for single remote transaction that is totally wrong. Since DNE2 cannot be released in Lustre-2.7, we have to land this one as temporary solution.\n\nThe patch 13392 fixed some memory leak issues related with the LFSCK (as described in LU-6138). So we need to land 13392 to master before Lustre-2.7 released.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
